  <description><![CDATA[<p>Grand Hotel Menaggio has the best location in town. It’s right on the lakefront and you can’t help but notice the hotel from the water – it’s old-world charm really stands out.</p>
<h2>Great base for exploring the Lake Como</h2>
<p>The centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/80beb49bbb7f416ba46131e7c79367b5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/80beb49bbb7f416ba46131e7c79367b5}" title="Menaggio">Menaggio</a> is only 300 metres away so you can easily explore the shops and bars or jump on a ferry and head out for the day. It’s a great base as ferries from here stop all around the lake.</p>
<h2>Relax outdoors</h2>
<p>The outside areas here are lovely. The gardens are beautifully maintained. The pool’s a nice spot to kick back and relax. You get views of the lake from here and you can see all the way to <a data-udi="umb://document/d3611d3782e0494ead59e534458bcdd6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d3611d3782e0494ead59e534458bcdd6}" title="Bellagio">Bellagio</a>. La Veranda's a great place for lunch, it’s close to the pool so you won’t have to venture far. They’ve got a good selection of light dishes and antipasti, plus a great cocktail menu.</p>]]></description>
